# Kurinto Mono JP - Monospace CJK fontpack for Lagrange

## TL;DR: Downloading and Setting Up the Fontpack

NOTE: the link is deliberately BROKEN, as I do not wish misbehaving bots to download this ~47MiB fontpack. Please, if you share this link, share it in a similarly broken fashion, or else link directly to _this_ page instead.

To fix the link, simply remove the Рђю.fooРђЮ from the end of it. Thanks!
=> gemini://shizuka.space/pub/KurintoMonoJP.fontpack.foo

These fonts are Free (Libre) and Open Source, under the SIL Open Font License Version 1.1 (see the Kurinto Fonts website, below, for details).

### Setting up Kurinto Mono JP in Lagrange

If you download the fontpack within the Lagrange Geminispace browser, it will directly offer to install the pack (making the fonts available for use in displaying capsules).

After installing the fontpack, you should open up Preferences, go to the Fonts section, and choose РђюKubuntu Mono JPРђЮ as the font for Preformatted text (and, optionally, for РђюMonospace fontРђЮ, which by default affects content served via Gopher or Nex, and other protocols that canРђЎt distinguish proportional text from fixed-width, but may include content such as ASCII art, or diagrams, that depend on the font being monospace).

The test Shogi board below should then display correctly. If it does not, you might go into the "Manage Fonts..." dialog in Lagrange, and disable any other currently-enabled fonts, and see if that makes a difference.

At least in Lagrange 1.20.7, there is no need to restartРђћthe pageРђЎs content should immediately reflect the change (possibly after switching to a different tab or page, and back again).

### Using the Fontpack for Other Purposes

This .fontpack file is just a zip archive of some TrueType fonts. After downloading the pack, you can rename it to .zip, and then extract it. However, you may wish to obtain a fuller set of typefaces that make up the Kurinto family, at:
=> https://www.kurinto.com/ Kurinto Fonts

In particular, note that Kurinto has CJK fonts for other languages/locales (HK, SC, TC, KR), so building your own fontpack based on those may suit your needs better, if Japanese is not the primary CJK language that you will be viewing.

## TestРђћDoes Your Client Correctly Display CJK in Monospace?

The following is a test display of a Shogi game board, copy/pasted from a game-in-progress at SGGS.
=> gemini://sggs.thegonz.net/ SGGS (the Simple Gemini Game Server)

If your CJK monospace font is set up correctly, all pieces, and the numbers on the right-hand side, should all be perfectly aligned, and you should clearly see kanji characters for the pieces, rather than uniform Рђюreplacement characterРђЮ boxes.

